Download logo A phone call was held today between the Minister of Foreign Affairs, H.E. Dr. Abdullatif bin Rashid Al-Zayani and the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Arab Republic of Egypt, H.E. Sameh Shoukry.  They reviewed brotherly relations between the two countries and the means of enhancing cooperation in various fields for the common interests of the two countries and their peoples.  The two sides also addressed developments at the political and security levels and underlined strengthening joint coordination towards current Arab and regional issues, in support of the process of joint Arab action for the interest of Arab countries and for the security and stability in the region.  Distributed by APO Group on behalf of Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Kingdom of Bahrain.